ListIsItemSortsAsBefore
/ A list is `: item` AND still sorts. list owns IOrderableValue (item does not),
/ so the inheritance is no-op for ordering — the sort produces the same shape
/ collections-are-data shipped.
- set %nums% = [3, 1, 2]
- sort %nums%
- get first item from %nums%, write to %first%
- assert %first% equals 1
- get last item from %nums%, write to %last%
- assert %last% equals 3
